Program: Great Lives
Title: Picasso
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b00pxn11
Last Broadcast Date: Fri 13 Oct 2017
Matthew Parris presents the biographical series in which his guests choose someone who has inspired their lives. Photographer David Bailey first saw Picasso's work in Look magazine in the 1950s - it was a revelation to him. He discusses the founder of Cubism's work and the enigma of the man himself, and their influence on him. Show less